<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="372" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Belgium/199a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Belgium (<persName corresp="#p_MF2" type="to">Mayer</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 610</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-27">June 27,
                                    1932</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Secretary of State refers to previous correspondence regarding
                                the President’s Proposal of June 20, 1931, for postponement of
                                intergovernmental debts and transmits for the information of the
                                Chargé d’Affaires copy of the “Agreement between the Kingdom of
                                Belgium and the United States of America, June 10, 1932”.<note n="21" xml:id="d372fn21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Annual Report of the Secretary of the
                                        Treasury</hi>, 1932, pp. 298–299.</note>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>